%20on%20who's%20responsible%20for%20AI%20upskilling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBecause%20the%20technology%20is%20changing%20so%20fast%2C%20traditional%20corporate%20training%20won't%20cut%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20have%20to%20learn%20a%20new%20thing%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20doing%20it%20on%20our%20own%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20Gadea%20wants%20the%20people%20who%20work%20for%20him%20to%20stay%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20AI.%20That%20might%20mean%20doing%20some%20homework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20workplace%20software%20company%20Envoy%20said%20the%20company%20is%20investing%20in%20AI%20training%20to%20help%20employees%20embrace%20the%20technology%20as%20a%20tool%20that%20can%20help%20them%20do%20better%20work.%20Yet%20he%20also%20believes%20workers%20have%20to%20take%20responsibility%20for%20learning%20outside%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20have%20to%20learn%20a%20new%20thing%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20doing%20it%20on%20our%20own%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Gadea%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20rewrites%20the%20instruction%20manual%20for%20job%20categories%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-tools-software-engineers-workplace-paralysis-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20new%20question%20is%20emerging%3A%20Who%20is%20responsible%20for%20making%20sure%20workers%20keep%20up%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20business%20leaders%20now%20view%20AI%20fluency%20as%20a%20baseline%20skill%2C%20bosses%20and%20workers%20are%20sometimes%20divided%20over%20how%20much%20responsibility%20belongs%20to%20employers%20and%20how%20much%20belongs%20to%20employees%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20tension%20showed%20up%20in%20a%20recent%20survey%20by%20the%20management%20and%20technology%20consultancy%20Emergn.%20About%20eight%20in%2010%20CEOs%20said%20employees%20should%20take%20responsibility%20for%20upskilling%20themselves%2C%20while%20a%20similar%20share%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftrainingmag.com%2Fthe-ai-skills-tug-of-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployee%20respondents%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20companies%20should%20provide%20AI%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Envoy%2C%20which%20helps%20companies%20manage%20office%20visitors%20and%20desk%20and%20room%20reservations%2C%20employees%20often%20demonstrate%20AI%20tools%20they've%20built%20and%20explain%20how%20they%20developed%20them%20during%20all-hands%20meetings%2C%20generally%20twice%20a%20month.%20Individual%20teams%20also%20meet%20regularly%20to%20discuss%20ways%20AI%20can%20improve%20workflows%2C%20such%20as%20automatically%20preparing%20account%20histories%20for%20sales%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20point%2C%20Gadea%20said%2C%20isn't%20to%20prove%20expertise.%20It's%20to%20normalize%20experimentation.%20Gadea%20said%20he%20frequently%20uses%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bimposter%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20to%20remind%20employees%20that%20the%20tech%20is%20new%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20literally%20saying%2C%20'Hey%20guys%2C%20it's%20OK.%20We're%20all%20learning%20together%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b5a06c4-3748-4a4c-a4f8-a04b2cc8a008%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20challenge%20of%20formal%20training%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFiguring%20out%20how%20to%20teach%20workers%20about%20AI%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20management%20challenges%20in%20recent%20years.%20Companies%20have%20tried%20a%20variety%20of%20methods%20during%20the%20traditional%209-5%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharkninjas-big-bet-4-day-ai-hackathon-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20hackathons%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-week-employee-training-claude-agents-vibe-coding-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20dashboards%20to%20illustrate%20AI%20use.%20Some%20workers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-learning-ai-tools-after-work-productivity-jobs-amazon-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espending%20nights%20and%20weekends%3C%2Fa%3E%20running%20experiments%20they%20can%20show%20off%20when%20they're%20back%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20not%20all%20workers%20are%20as%20excited%20about%20AI%20as%20the%20boss%20might%20be.%20Research%20shows%20a%20gap%20between%20employees'%20and%20employers'%20eagerness%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutives-adopting-ai-higher-rates-than-workers-research-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eembrace%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutives-adopting-ai-higher-rates-than-workers-research-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupskilling-new-side-hustle-for-software-engineers-ai-era-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkplace%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20long%20been%20a%20shared%20responsibility%20between%20employers%20and%20employees.%20About%2060%25%20of%20workplace%20learning%20tends%20to%20be%20self-directed%20through%20resources%20like%20articles%20and%20videos%2C%20said%20RJ%20Bannister%2C%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20at%20the%20executive%20compensation%20and%20corporate%20governance%20consultancy%20Farient%20Advisors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2030%25%20comes%20from%20hands-on%20experience%2C%20including%20working%20with%20colleagues%20and%20on%20projects%2C%20and%20about%20is%2010%25%20from%20formal%20training%20sessions%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20can%20make%20the%20process%20more%20efficient%20by%20letting%20people%20work%20through%20more%20topics%20in%20less%20time%2C%20Bannister%20said.%20Yet%2C%20he%20added%2C%20workers%20still%20need%20to%20apply%20what%20they%20learned%20to%20make%20it%20stick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBannister%20compares%20worker%20training%20and%20development%20to%20how%20a%20company%20spends%20money%20to%20maintain%20factory%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20another%20way%2C%20he%20said%2C%20of%20making%20workers%20feel%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20new%20technology%20like%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20a%20part%20of%20a%20solution%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20just%20seeing%20it%20solely%20as%20a%20threat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20private%20crypto%20exchange%20GoDark%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Denis%20Dariotis%20said%20many%20employees%20simply%20learn%20by%20doing.%20In%20part%2C%20that's%20because%20while%20they%20might%20be%20experienced%20software%20engineers%2C%20most%20didn't%20start%20their%20careers%20in%20crypto%20trading%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20team%20that's%20sort%20of%20just%20thrown%20into%20the%20deep%20end%2C%20and%20then%20they%20have%20to%20figure%20it%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Dariotis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoDark%20doesn't%20require%20formal%20AI%20training%20for%20its%20roughly%20three%20dozen%20workers.%20To%20keep%20up%2C%20employees%20share%20articles%20and%20ideas%20in%20Slack%2C%20sometimes%20after%20hours%2C%20though%20Dariotis%2C%20who%20also%20runs%20the%20crypto%20infrastructure%20firm%20GoQuant%2C%20said%20he%20doesn't%20expect%20people%20to%20spend%20their%20evenings%20learning%20after%20regularly%20putting%20in%2012-hour%20days.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Dariotis%20said%20he%20doesn't%20mind%20seeing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20everyone%20has%20this%20natural%20interest%20in%20the%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22669e2275-4a81-4e86-94db-acd7a19a8639%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELearning%20at%20the%20pace%20of%20AI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20limited%20time%20in%20the%20workday%2C%20another%20challenge%20is%20ensuring%20that%20any%20company%20training%20stays%20current.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20can't%20rely%20on%20quarterly%20training%20sessions%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-creating-identity-crisis-for-software-engineers-coders-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20AI%20models%20and%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20arrive%20every%20few%20weeks%2C%20said%20Kathy%20Gersch%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20change-management%20firm%20Kotter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20training%20on%20a%20process%20or%20how%20to%20use%20a%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20what%20is%20current%20this%20month%20might%20be%20different%20by%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20relying%20solely%20on%20formal%20classes%2C%20companies%20should%20build%20systems%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-software-engineer-microsoft-ai-not-threat-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehelp%20employees%20continuously%20share%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20they're%20discovering%20with%20one%20another%2C%20Gersch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20corporate%20training%20is%20offered%2C%20it's%20often%20too%20generic%20and%20not%20tied%20to%20a%20company%20or%20a%20job%2C%20said%20Mark%20Ma%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20School%20of%20Business.%20That%20can%20make%20it%20less%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gadea%2C%20learning%20AI%20isn't%20only%20about%20succeeding%20at%20Envoy.%20Workers%20who%20want%20to%20move%20to%20another%20company%2C%20he%20said%2C%20will%20increasingly%20be%20expected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwelcome-age-ai-sprawl-too-many-tools-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edemonstrate%20proficiency%20with%20AI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGadea%20said%20that's%20yet%20another%20reason%20to%20put%20in%20the%20work%20%E2%80%94%20both%20on%20and%20off%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20AI%20experience%20at%20work%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-workers-employers-upskilling-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783330621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4adf3ce3bd3a50082c0669%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-workers-employers-upskilling-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20embracing%20hackathons%2C%20training%20sessions%2C%20and%20mentoring%20from%209-5.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20you're%20off%20the%20hook%20on%20nights%20and%20weekends.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20warns%20of%20interceptor%20missile%20shortage%20as%2014%20killed%20in%20Kyiv%20region%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783330543000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Face%2Fbranded_news%2F1200%2Fcpsprodpb%2F528b%2Flive%2Fe5134170-78ee-11f1-b5ef-67aee6df60e2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcewqqnd7zdwo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Zelensky%20says%20Sunday's%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20Russian%20attack%26quot%3B%20consisted%20of%2068%20missiles%20and%20351%20strike%20drones.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcewqqnd7zdwo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26lt%3Ba%20href