%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-americas-battlefield-dominance-is-under-serious-threat-11733110%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anurag%20Kashyap%20Boards%20Rotterdam-Premiered%20Bangladeshi%20Drama%20%E2%80%98Delupi%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783329377000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236802252%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian%20auteur%20Anurag%20Kashyap%20has%20come%20on%20board%20as%20presenter%20of%20Bangladeshi%20drama%20%E2%80%9CDelupi%2C%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20film%20set%20to%20carry%20the%20%E2%80%9CAnurag%20Kashyap%20Presents%E2%80%9D%20banner%20across%20its%20release%20and%20promotional%20campaigns%20going%20forward.%20%E2%80%9CDelupi%E2%80%9D%20had%20its%20international%20premiere%20in%20the%20Bright%20Future%20section%20of%20the%20International%20Film%20Festival%20Rotterdam%20(IFFR)%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20premiere%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20took%20a%2050%25%20paycut%20when%20I%20got%20laid%20off%20from%20Meta%20and%20started%20a%20coaching%20business.%20The%20transition%20was%20hard%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20better%20all%20around.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221318%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20who%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20business%20attire%20smiling%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ae599e3bd3a50082c0683%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22992%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20building%20a%20life%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20escape%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Chikara%20Kennedy%2C%20who%20launched%20a%20coaching%20business%20and%20moved%20to%20Mexico%20after%20her%20Meta%20layoff.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Chikara%20Kennedy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChikara%20Kennedy%20worked%20as%20an%20HR%20manager%20at%20Meta%20before%20her%20layoff%20in%202023.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20started%20a%20coaching%20business%20in%202024%20and%20now%20earns%20about%20half%20of%20her%20old%20salary.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoving%20to%20Mexico%20helped%20her%20reduce%20expenses%20and%20improve%20her%20overall%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Chikara%20Kennedy%2C%20the%2043-year-old%20CEO%20of%20Chikara%20Power%20Coaching%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Mexico.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Kennedy's%20income%20and%20employment%20with%20documentation%20and%20edited%20her%20words%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20launching%20my%20own%20company%20in%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-hr-manager-got-laid-off-too-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20worked%20at%20Meta%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20nearly%20five%20years%20as%20a%20senior%20HR%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20my%20base%20salary%20was%20roughly%20%24250%2C000%2C%20and%20with%20bonus%20and%20restricted%20stock%20options%2C%20I%20was%20making%20over%20%24300%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20high-income%2C%20very%20structured%20corporate%20role%2C%20and%20my%20pay%20was%20predictable%20in%20a%20way%20that%20felt%20stable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20in%202023%2C%20everything%20shifted.%20I%20got%20divorced%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-hr-manager-got-laid-off-too-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20got%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20turned%2040%20%E2%80%94%20all%20within%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20any%20indication%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20get%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20it%20was%20very%20traumatic.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20was%20shaken%20by%20the%20job%20loss%3B%20I%20felt%20anxious%20about%20the%20uncertainty%20ahead%20and%20was%20having%20meltdowns%20about%20my%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%202024%2C%20I'd%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-career-coaching-side-hustle-earn-extra-money-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estart%20my%20own%20coaching%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db25614d-e290-414f-bede-304e9fcf3541%5C%22%3EI%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20downsize%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20starting%20my%20business%2C%20not%20knowing%20if%20it%20would%20be%20as%20profitable%20as%20the%20job%20I%20had%20before%2C%20I%20started%20to%20look%20for%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-increase-savings-early-retirement-expenses-financial-freedom-fire-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereduce%20my%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20improve%20my%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20savings%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20trying%20to%20maintain%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-washington-dc-for-san-diego-california-better-fit-lifestyle-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elifestyle%20in%20DC%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20expensive%20apartment%2C%20wasn't%20a%20good%20idea%20as%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20where%20my%20income%20felt%20less%20stable%20and%20I%20wasn't%20getting%20a%20paycheck%20every%20two%20weeks.%20My%20rent%20in%20downtown%20DC%20alone%20was%20over%20%243%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20on%20the%20beach%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4af6e0e3bd3a50082c06b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22898%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKennedy%20loves%20living%20close%20to%20the%20beach%20in%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Chikara%20Kennedy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20money%20would%20feel%20tight.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-rural-town-save-money-short-term-benefits-sacrifices-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMoving%20somewhere%20cheaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20like%20a%20fun%2C%20viable%20option%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20lifestyle-wise%2C%20but%20also%20as%20a%20way%20to%20reduce%20my%20expenses%20and%20reset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20make%20life%20cheaper%2C%20I%20met%20a%20stranger%20in%20DC%20at%20a%20nail%20salon.%20We%20started%20talking%20about%20life%2C%20entrepreneurship%2C%20and%20how%20expensive%20it%20was%20to%20live%20in%20DC.%20She%20told%20me%20she%20was%20thinking%20about%20moving%20to%20the%20beach%20in%20Mexico%20and%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20you%20should%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I%20had%20ever%20met%20her%2C%20but%20something%20about%20it%20clicked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9ec7eee-63fa-45e7-a8d7-581e347de6fe%5C%22%3EAfter%20my%20layoff%20and%20starting%20my%20business%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20Mexico%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202024%2C%20I%20packed%20up%20my%20belongings%2C%20put%20my%2015-year-old%20car%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20things%20in%20storage%2C%20took%20four%20suitcases%20with%20me%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-us-moved-to-mexico-american-dream-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Mexico%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20debt%20or%20a%20car%20payment.%20My%20thinking%20was%20that%20if%20I%20didn't%20like%20it%2C%20I%20could%20always%20move%20back.%20I%20knew%20the%20only%20thing%20truly%20secure%20was%20my%20ability%20to%20adapt%20and%20rebuild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20wouldn't%20I%20take%20the%20opportunity%20to%20live%20a%20different%20lifestyle%2C%20reduce%20my%20expenses%2C%20and%20give%20myself%20the%20time%20and%20space%20to%20focus%20on%20creating%20and%20reinventing%20myself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a96e94a-d92a-4791-857d-21d2577aeff7%5C%22%3EI%20now%20make%20roughly%2050%25%20of%20what%20I%20used%20to%20make%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20adjustment%20was%20learning%20to%20live%20without%20the%20psychological%20safety%20of%20a%20predictable%20paycheck%20after%20nearly%2020%20years%20in%20corporate%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20challenging%20as%20I'm%20not%20able%20to%20save%20or%20invest%20the%20way%20I%20did%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20times%20when%20my%20business%20has%20slowed%2C%20and%20I've%20re-examined%20my%20budget%2C%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20cut%20back.%20Right%20now%2C%20my%20rent%20is%20close%20to%20%241%2C700%20for%20a%20two-bedroom%2C%20and%20I'm%20considering%20moving%20to%20a%20one-bedroom%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20have%20a%20little%20more%20wiggle%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20unlike%20in%20DC%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20a%20car%2C%20and%20I%20spend%20very%20little%20on%20shopping.%20It's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheapest-cities-in-the-world-to-live-expats-europe-asia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escaled-back%20lifestyle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20live%20across%20from%20the%20beach%20and%20I%20love%20it.%20I%20walk%20most%20places%2C%20and%20spend%20far%20less%20on%20consumerism%2C%20status%20spending%2C%20commuting%2C%20and%20convenience-based%20living%20than%20I%20did%20during%20my%20corporate%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20health%20insurance.%20I'd%20previously%20had%20great%20healthcare%20through%20my%20employer%2C%20so%20when%20I%20got%20laid%20off%2C%20losing%20that%20was%20a%20big%20concern%20for%20me%2C%20especially%20being%20over%2040.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20it%20feels%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-retired-early-abroad-mexico-mistakes-made-first-year-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20affordable%20in%20Mexico%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20I'm%20able%20to%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket.%20My%20healthcare%20is%20better%20than%20what%20I%20had%20in%20the%20US%2C%20too%2C%20and%20I%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%20more%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20make%20less%20money%20today%2C%20many%20aspects%20of%20my%20life%20have%20improved%20dramatically%3A%20my%20health%2C%20stress%20levels%2C%20flexibility%2C%20relationships%2C%20and%20overall%20quality%20of%20life.%20My%20everyday%20life%20now%20reflects%20the%20kind%20of%20freedom%20I%20used%20to%20only%20experience%20during%20short%20vacations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20go%20to%20work%20every%20day%2C%20come%20home%2C%20go%20to%20sleep%2C%20and%20wait%20for%20the%20weekend%20or%20vacation.%20Now%2C%20even%20on%20less%20income%2C%20I%20can%20go%20to%20the%20beach%20on%20Tuesday%20if%20I%20want%20to.%20I'm%20in%20the%20sunshine%2C%20walking%20more%2C%20and%20swimming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20wasn't%20just%20a%20financial%20reinvention.%20It%20was%20emotional%20and%20identity-based%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22258c726d-89f7-453c-921b-4051cf2682fe%5C%22%3EThough%20I%20make%20less%2C%20I%20feel%20better%20all%20around%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20entrepreneur%20has%20been%20a%20good%20growth%20opportunity%20for%20me.%20It's%20made%20me%20think%20more%20about%20what%20I%20truly%20want%20and%20why.%20It's%20made%20me%20think%20more%20about%20networking%20and%20different%20ways%20of%20making%20income%2C%20and%20it's%20allowed%20me%20to%20live%20a%20more%20authentic%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20realizations%20for%20me%20was%20that%20modern%20stability%20looks%20very%20different%20than%20what%20many%20of%20us%20were%20taught.%20I'd%20spent%20years%20building%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuccessful%26quot%3B%20life%2C%20but%20when%20divorce%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-cutting-jobs-again-better-off-after-being-laid-off-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elayoff%3C%2Fa%3E%20happened%20close%20together%2C%20it%20forced%20me%20to%20reevaluate%20what%20security%20actually%20meant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20expected%20to%20always%20work%20corporate%2C%20and%20to%20retire%20from%20it%20with%20a%20pension.%20Being%20an%20entrepreneur%20was%20never%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20though%20it's%20not%20what%20I%20thought%20my%20life%20would%20look%20like%2C%20I'm%20much%20happier%20even%20while%20making%20less.%20My%20mental%20health%20is%20better%2C%20and%20I'm%20more%20open%20to%20new%20things%2C%20like%20meeting%20new%20people.%20I'm%20more%20adjusted.%20I'm%20more%20adventurous%20than%20I%20was%2C%20and%20I%20really%20feel%20like%20I'm%20living%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20get%20to%20work%20with%20people%20I%20want%20to%20work%20with%2C%20I%20create%20my%20schedule%20and%20create%20time%20for%20things%20that%20are%20important%20to%20me%20like%20exercise%2C%20yoga%2C%20and%20being%20on%20the%20beach.%20I%20used%20to%20work%20to%20escape%20my%20life.%20Now%20I'm%20building%20a%20life%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20escape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20how%20you%20adjusted%20your%20lifestyle%20after%20a%20paycut%3F%20Contact%20this%20editor%2C%20Debbie%20Strong%2C%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adstrong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Edstrong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-laid-off-from-meta-moved-mexico-reduced-expenses-paycut-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783329361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4ae599e3bd3a50082c0683%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-laid-off-from-meta-moved-mexico-reduced-expenses-paycut-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20her%20Meta%20layoff%2C%20Chikaraa%20Kennedy%20launched%20a%20coaching%20business%20and%20moved%20to%20Mexico%20%E2%80%94%20where%20she%20spends%20less%20and%20has%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alyshia%20Hull)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google's%20status%20as%20the%20dream%20tech%20job%20is%20changing.%20FOMO%20over%20AI%20salaries%20is%20only%20one%20reason%20why.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223111%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20office%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46944465e65d39ff1c906d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle's%20reputation%20as%20a%20dream%20employer%20is%20evolving%20in%20the%20AI%20era.%3Cp%3EStefan%20Rousseau%2FPA%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20has%20long%20been%20regarded%20as%20a%20dream%20employer%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20say%20that%20reputation%20has%20become%20more%20complicated.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20startups%2C%20layoffs%2C%20and%20the%20desire%20for%20greater%20impact%20are%20reshaping%20career%20decisions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarning%20nearly%20%241%20million%20a%20year%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20keep%20Yousuf%20Imran%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202026%2C%20Imran%20earned%20%24986%2C000%20as%20a%20Google%20account%20executive%2C%20largely%20from%20sales%20commissions%20on%20top%20of%20a%20roughly%20%24170%2C000%20base%20salary.%20Even%20still%2C%20he%20couldn't%20help%20but%20notice%20the%20potential%20for%20%26quot%3Blife-changing%20money%26quot%3B%20the%20AI%20boom%20was%20creating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-made-one-million-explains-why-left-big-tech2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutside%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20pays%20very%20well%2C%20but%20the%20equity%20packages%20at%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%20are%20in%20a%20different%20universe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Imran%2C%2041%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20seeing%20talented%20colleagues%20get%20laid%20off%20over%20the%20previous%20few%20years%20made%20him%20less%20confident%20about%20his%20long-term%20job%20security.%20In%20April%2C%20after%20building%20AI%20side%20projects%20in%20his%20spare%20time%2C%20Imran%20left%20Google%20to%20launch%20an%20AI%20sales%20tools%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Google's%20reputation%20as%20a%20workplace%20was%20almost%20as%20famous%20as%20its%20search%20engine.%20Its%20sprawling%20campuses%2C%20generous%20perks%2C%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20shape%20products%20used%20by%20billions%20of%20people%20made%20it%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20coveted%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20reputation%20hasn't%20disappeared%2C%20but%20for%20some%20employees%2C%20it%20has%20become%20more%20complicated.%20Interviews%20with%2012%20current%20and%20former%20Google%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20including%20six%20who%20recently%20left%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20suggest%20the%20AI%20boom%20has%20created%20opportunities%20that%20have%20become%20too%20compelling%20for%20some%20Googlers%20to%20ignore.%20In%20recent%20weeks%2C%20the%20company%20has%20lost%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-suddenly-losing-ai-talent-anthropic-openai-pre-ipo-equity-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-profile%20AI%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20AI%20boom%20isn't%20the%20only%20reason.%20Years%20of%20layoffs%2C%20shifts%20in%20workplace%20culture%2C%20and%20other%20changes%20have%20also%20led%20employees%20across%20the%20company%20to%20question%20whether%20it%20remains%20the%20best%20place%20to%20build%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283104d56-74b2-47be-9a40-97edecb47d9e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoogle%20no%20longer%20feels%20like%20the%20safe%20bet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20was%20the%20world's%20most%20attractive%20employer%20for%20business%20students%20for%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fobserver.com%2F2022%2F11%2Fgoogle-is-no-longer-the-most-attractive-employer-globally-for-business-students%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20decade%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20employer-branding%20firm%20Universum.%20But%20in%202022%2C%20it%20fell%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-business-students-want-to-work-for-universum-2022-11%232-google-29%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esecond%20behind%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20US%20specifically%2C%20Google%20fell%20from%20first%20among%20business%20students%20in%202023%20to%20fifth%20in%20the%20firm's%20most%20recent%20survey%2C%20though%20it%20remained%20the%20most%20attractive%20employer%20among%20IT%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20factors%20matter%20more%20to%20current%20and%20prospective%20employees%20than%20job%20security.%20Between%20its%20founding%20in%201998%20and%202022%2C%20large-scale%20layoffs%20were%20rare%20at%20Google.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20about%2012%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20roughly%206%25%20of%20its%20workforce.%20Smaller%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20and%20voluntary%20buyouts%20followed%20as%20Google%20shifted%20resources%20toward%20AI%2C%20reduced%20layers%20of%20management%2C%20and%20recalibrated%20after%20pandemic-era%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yousuf%20Imran%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46953ce3bd3a50082bfa38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22864%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYousuf%20Imran%20said%20the%20AI%20boom%20and%20recent%20layoffs%20helped%20shape%20his%20decision%20to%20leave%20Google.%3Cp%3EYousuf%20Imran%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20employees%2C%20the%20repeated%20cuts%20fundamentally%20changed%20how%20they%20thought%20about%20the%20stability%20of%20a%20career%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20six%20months%20after%20Joslyn%20Orgill%20started%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-quit-tech-job-phd-grad-school-career-change-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20engineer%20at%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20its%202023%20layoffs.%20Though%20Orgill%20kept%20her%20job%2C%20she%20said%20the%20layoffs%20were%20among%20the%20reasons%20she%20left%20last%20year%20to%20pursue%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20computer%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20M.%20LaSane%20was%20among%20the%20employees%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-return-office-buyouts-employees-leaked-memo-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccepted%20a%20buyout%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20She%20had%20already%20considered%20focusing%20on%20the%20career%20coaching%20business%20she'd%20started%20three%20years%20earlier%2C%20but%20said%20the%20repeated%20layoffs%20made%20leaving%20Google%20feel%20less%20risky%20than%20it%20might%20have%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%20%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221378e4b3-eef6-417b-8af1-0c7d7b2607b7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20for%20a%20bigger%20impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20still%20offers%20many%20of%20the%20generous%20perks%20that%20helped%20make%20it%20famous%20as%20an%20employer.%20But%20some%20employees%20say%20the%20experience%20of%20working%20there%20has%20changed%20on%20the%20margins%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20scaled%20back%20some%20office%20amenities%20and%20budgets%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cuts-perks-leaked-memo-google-cost-cutting-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereducing%20the%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20certain%20office%20caf%C3%A9s%20in%202023%20as%20part%20of%20cost-cutting%20efforts.%20Some%20employees%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-perks-benefits-staff-workers-layoffs-cutting-back-employees-socials-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esaid%20budgets%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20certain%20travel%2C%20team%20events%2C%20and%20holiday%20celebrations%20have%20tightened%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogles-crackdown-on-remote-work-rto-frustrates-employees-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-from-home%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20become%20more%20restrictive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20employees%2C%20one%20of%20the%20very%20qualities%20that%20made%20Google%20such%20an%20attractive%20employer%20%E2%80%94%20its%20scale%20and%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20also%20made%20it%20harder%20to%20see%20the%20direct%20impact%20of%20their%20own%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%2C%20you're%20one%20piece%20of%20a%20very%20large%20machine%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Aashna%20Doshi%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-software-engineer-podcaster-quit-ai-tech-startup-job-market-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20Google%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20launch%20an%20AI%20startup.%20%26quot%3BI%20craved%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%2C%20move%20fast%2C%20and%20see%20the%20direct%20results%20of%20my%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aashna%20Doshi%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a46959265e65d39ff1c909f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAashna%20Doshi%20left%20Google%20in%20May%20to%20build%20an%20AI%20startup.%3Cp%3EAashna%20Doshi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Doshi%2C%20the%20chance%20to%20build%20something%20of%20her%20own%20ultimately%20outweighed%20the%20security%20of%20staying%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20scarier%20version%20of%20this%20decision%20wasn't%20leaving%20Google%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20staying%20and%20always%20wondering%20what%20could%20have%20been.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3565ab2-71ff-47b1-8a84-cb1cac308036%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20changed%20the%20equation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20changes%20reshaping%20Google%20aren't%20unique%20to%20the%20company.%20Tech%20workers%20across%20the%20industry%20have%20navigated%20layoffs%2C%20shifting%20workplace%20policies%2C%20and%20the%20rapid%20rise%20of%20AI.%20For%20many%20employees%2C%20Google%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20desirable%20places%20to%20build%20a%20career%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic%20race%20toward%20potential%20IPOs%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20pre-IPO%20equity%20has%20become%20a%20powerful%20lure%20for%20some%20workers.%20Career%20coach%20Sundeep%20Teki%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20nearly%20every%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-everybody-wants-to-work-at-anthropic-or-openai-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20job%20seeker%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20speaks%20with%20wants%20to%20work%20at%20one%20of%20the%20two%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20some%20Google%20employees%20have%20voiced%20frustration%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-smaller-pay-bumps-recent-all-hands-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmaller%20compensation%20increases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company's%20six-figure%20salaries%20and%20generous%20stock%20grants%20remain%20the%20envy%20of%20much%20of%20the%20corporate%20world.%20A%20Google%20spokesperson%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-talent-wars-anthropic-jumper-shazeer-karpathy-openai-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompany%20remains%20confident%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20ability%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20former%20Googlers%2C%20however%2C%20even%20Google's%20generous%20compensation%20isn't%20enough%20to%20outweigh%20the%20opportunities%20created%20by%20the%20AI%20boom%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that's%20joining%20a%20fast-growing%20AI%20company%20or%20building%20one%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20only%20way%20to%20get%20real%20upside%20in%20this%20AI%20moment%20is%20equity%2C%20at%20some%20point%2C%20you%20ask%20yourself%20whether%20the%20equity%20should%20be%20in%20your%20own%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Imran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20working%20in%20tech%3F%20Reach%20reporter%20Jacob%20Zinkula%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-leaving-ai-openai-anthropic-big-tech-jobs-careers-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783329302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4694601bba93485607adc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-leaving-ai-openai-anthropic-big-tech-jobs-careers-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Recent%20AI%20departures%20put%20Google%20in%20the%20spotlight.%20Interviews%20with%20current%20and%20former%20Googlers%20reveal%20a%20broader%20shift%20in%20why%20employees%20are%20leaving.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Small%20businesses%20hired%20AI%20to%20save%20money.%20Now%20they're%20budgeting%20for%20its%20bad%20habits.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20view%20of%20senior%20saleswoman%20using%20computer%20while%20standing%20at%20checkout%20in%20hardware%20store%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ec546a25092c74cc9ff79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMaskot%2FGetty%20Images%2FMaskot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20adoption%20among%20small%20businesses%20is%20rising%2C%20driven%20by%20cost-saving%20and%20efficiency%20benefits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20small%20business%20used%20AI%20to%20weather%20tariff%20impacts%2C%20but%20also%20ran%20up%20an%20accidental%20big%20bill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnother%20firm%20uses%20AI%20for%20different%20assistant%20functions%2C%20which%20sometimes%20results%20in%20silly%20encounters.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESparkles%20Homes%2C%20which%20makes%20a%20bevy%20of%20bedazzled%20products%20for%20discount%20stores%20like%20HomeGoods%2C%20was%20under%20pressure%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-do-trump-tariffs-work-what-are-tariffs-trump-plan-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariffs%20hit%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-helps-us-businesses-manage-supreme-court-tariff-impacts-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esupply%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E.%20AI%20ended%20up%20being%20a%20lifesaver%20for%20the%20business%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eautomating%20various%20processes%20and%20reducing%20marketing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20worried%20about%20AI%20taking%20jobs%2C%20but%2C%20for%20us%20specifically%2C%20that'd%20be%20the%20only%20reason%20why%20the%20company%20is%20still%20in%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Brandon%20Lind.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20why%20the%20five%20people%20that%20still%20work%20for%20me%20do%20still%20have%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20growing%20cohort%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-cuban-ai-era-job-advice-look-at-small-businesses-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esmall%20business%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20using%20AI%20to%20cut%20costs%20and%20keep%20things%20running.%20A%20US%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20survey%20found%20that%2058%25%20of%20small%20businesses%20used%20AI%20in%202025%2C%20up%20from%2023%25%20in%202023.%20But%20AI%20adoption%20also%20carries%20unexpected%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Amy%20Wood%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Flint%20Avenue%20Marketing%2C%20a%20small%20boutique%20agency%20in%20Lubbock%2C%20Texas%2C%20AI%20has%20been%20useful%20for%20website%20work%20and%20even%20staffing.%20She%20uses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-doubled-income-save-me-fifteen-hours-each-week-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20AI%20assistant%3C%2Fa%3E%20named%20%26quot%3BRachel%26quot%3B%20to%20man%20the%20phones%20at%20their%20remote-first%20office%2C%20and%20a%20sales%20assistant%20named%20%26quot%3BSonny%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20her%20track%20down%20leads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20led%20to%20some%20snafus.%20Sonny%20sent%20an%20obviously%20AI-generated%20email%20to%20a%20new%20lead%20recently%2C%20who%20wrote%20back%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Blong%20diatribe%26quot%3B%20making%20fun%20of%20the%20AI.%20Rachel%20had%20a%20tendency%20to%20console%20callers%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20not%20upset%3B%20Wood%20had%20to%20tell%20her%20to%20stop%20apologizing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20just%20set%20it%20up%20and%20set%20it%20and%20forget%20it%2C%20it%20will%20create%20chaos%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20amplify%20whatever%20chaos%20you%20have%20happening%20in%20your%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20businesses%20are%20learning%20that%20AI%20is%20not%20a%20simple%20plug-and-play%20productivity%20booster.%20It%20can%20speed%20up%20processes%20and%20make%20life%20easier%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-spending-roi-concerns-tokenmaxxing-uber-coo-andrew-macdonald-reaction-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecreate%20surprise%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20awkward%20errors%2C%20and%20an%20uneasy%20reliance%20on%20software%20that%20business%20owners%20don't%20fully%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7db6266-85a2-44bd-b1a6-c2cef5572f8f%5C%22%3EHow%20small%20businesses%20are%20adapting%20to%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAra%20Kharazian%2C%20the%20lead%20economist%20at%20Ramp%2C%20said%20that%20small%20firms%20are%20still%20less%20likely%20to%20use%20AI%20than%20their%20larger%20colleagues%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20when%20they%20do%2C%20they%20do%20use%20it%20more%2C%20and%20they%20use%20it%20more%20intensely.%26quot%3B%20Small%20businesses%20adopting%20AI%20are%20paying%20a%20median%20of%20about%20%2421%20per%20employee%2C%20compared%20with%20%2411%20across%20businesses%20of%20all%20sizes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FN37o3%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FN37o3%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFirms%20with%200%20to%2049%20workers%20spent%2C%20on%20average%2C%20%24607%20per%20worker%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlantafed.org%2Fresearch-and-data%2Fpublications%2Fpolicy-hub-macroblog%2F2026%2F05%2F06%2Fhow-much-firms-spending-on-ai-and-what-will-happen-to-headcounts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Atlanta%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202026%2C%20they%20expect%20to%20spend%20%241%2C034.%20Small%20businesses%20are%20also%20increasingly%20paying%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmulti-agent-systems-are-the-next-big-thing-in-ai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20one%20AI%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20Chi%20Mac%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20a%20report%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpmorganchase.com%2Finstitute%2Fall-topics%2Fbusiness-growth-and-entrepreneurship%2Funderstanding-ai-use-by-small-businesses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJPMorganChase%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20some%20owners%20are%20starting%20to%20think%20about%20AI%20the%20way%20they%20think%20about%20other%20operating%20expenses.%20Bill%20Belknap%2C%20the%20president%20of%20AEONRG%2C%20a%20construction%20contracting%20firm%2C%20said%20he%20includes%20AI%20costs%20in%20his%20overhead%20for%20projects.%20Wood%20now%20sets%20aside%20%24500%20a%20month%20as%20a%20buffer%20in%20case%20AI%20prices%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20worried%20more%20that%20I%20would%20get%20something%20deployed%20and%20then%20get%20all%20dependent%20on%20it%20as%20part%20of%20my%20workflow%2C%20and%20then%20the%20prices%20jack%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20spent%20so%20much%20time%20getting%20our%20processes%20and%20everything%20in%20order%2C%20we%20would%20hate%20to%20lose%20that%20investment%20if%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20the%20platform%20doubles%20in%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECPA%20Mark%20Gallegos%20said%20he%20sees%20smaller%20businesses%20inheriting%20AI%20costs%20through%20the%20software%20they%20already%20use%2C%20which%20have%20incorporated%20new%20AI%20functions.%20A%20browser%20might%20offer%20to%20summarize%20or%20turbocharge%20a%20spreadsheet%2C%20and%20workers%20click%20in%20without%20thinking%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20they%20don't%20understand%20that%20there%20is%20an%20additional%20cost%2C%20just%20like%20anything%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Gallegos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20pre-%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenterprise-ai-spending-grows-openai-leads-rbc-reveals-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epost-ChatGPT%20divide%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20how%20quickly%20small%20businesses%20adopt%20AI.%20A%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20report%20found%20that%20for%20firms%20started%20in%202023%2C%20it%20took%20nearly%20two%20years%20for%2010%25%20of%20them%20to%20begin%20paying%20for%20at%20least%20one%20AI%20service.%20Firms%20started%20in%202025%20took%20just%20six%20months.%20Millennial%20small%20business%20owners%20are%20adopting%20AI%20at%20the%20highest%20rate%2C%20followed%20by%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Gen%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20small%20businesses%20on%20the%20AI%20train%20are%20plowing%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20folks%20who%20are%20active%20adopters%20are%20generally%20enthusiastic%20and%20actually%20tell%20us%20they%20want%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tammy%20Halevy%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20small%20business%20organization%20Reimagine%20Main%20Street.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20more%20use%20cases%2C%20they%20want%20more%20automation%2C%20they%20want%20more%20and%20more%20and%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dfe329ba-3c91-43e3-b460-c6663cd71d01%5C%22%3EStriking%20the%20right%20AI%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20a%20gamble%20on%20AI%20is%20still%20riskier%20for%20smaller%20businesses%20that%20get%20by%20on%20razor-thin%20margins.%20That's%20leading%20some%20to%20enact%20their%20own%20guardrails%20on%20the%20fly%2C%20whether%20it's%20telling%20AI%20receptionists%20to%20chill%20out%20or%20creating%20careful%20guides%20to%20tokens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELind%20learned%20that%20the%20hard%20way%3A%20He%20once%20accidentally%20spent%20%241%2C000%20on%20AI%20while%20trying%20to%20generate%20stock%20images.%20His%20LLM%20began%20creating%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20pictures%2C%20burning%20through%20tokens%20along%20the%20way.%20He%20responded%20by%20putting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-token-economy-spending-workplace-budgets-usage-caps-software-engineer-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20daily%20spending%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20company's%20AI%20usage%20and%20giving%20workers%20an%20AI%20guide%20with%20adages%20such%20as%20treating%20tokens%20like%20money%20and%20starting%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finworld-ceo-cuts-ai-model-prices-to-aid-consumer-startups-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleast%20expensive%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20do%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20need%20to%20be%20careful%20on%20what%20we're%20spending%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20we're%20using%20AI%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20benefit%20us%2C%20and%20not%20something%20that's%20going%20to%20put%20us%20in%20a%20worse%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWood%20said%20that%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20when%20her%20business%20received%20an%20influx%20of%20calls%2C%20she%20had%20to%20top%20up%20tokens%20to%20power%20her%20receptionist%20%E2%80%94%20a%20situation%20that%20wouldn't%20happen%20(hopefully)%20with%20a%20human%20manning%20the%20phones.%20But%20even%20if%20costs%20rise%2C%20she'll%20stay%20all%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20want%20to%20hear%20that%20necessarily%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20less%20than%20hiring%20someone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20hired%20a%20receptionist%20and%20a%20salesperson%20and%20an%20SEO%20person%20and%20an%20executive%20assistant%2C%20all%20of%20those%20positions%20are%20pretty%20much%20handled%20by%20AI%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-transforms-small-businesses-but-challenges-persist-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783329301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ec56a360acd489560c103%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-transforms-small-businesses-but-challenges-persist-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20has%20been%20a%20boon%20for%20many%20small%20businesses.%20It's%20also%20led%20to%20accidental%20spending%20and%20awkward%20encounters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jkaplan%40businessinsider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20Police%20Bust%20Interstate%20Racket%20Selling%20Fake%20Governmentt%20IDs%2C%202%20Arrested%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Police%20said%20the%20accused%20operated%20the%20website%20by%20asking%20customers%20to%20first%20recharge%20a%20digital%20wallet%20before%20placing%20orders.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783329239000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-police-bust-interstate-racket-selling-fake-governmentt-ids-2-arrested-11733067%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Police%20said%20the%20accused%20