s-clash-over-telangana-irrigation-project-ktrs-drought-warning-blame-game-11732760%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkaleshwaram-politics-clash-over-telangana-irrigation-project-ktrs-drought-warning-blame-game-11732760%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20spent%2020%20years%20teaching%20people%20to%20communicate.%20Phone%20anxiety%20has%20never%20been%20worse.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mary%20Jane%20Copps%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42fa6de218c3b62535f035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMary%20Jane%20Copps%2C%20a%20conversation%20coach%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Phone%20Lady%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20anxiety%20around%20phone%20calls%20is%20prevalent%20among%20young%20professionals.%3Cp%3EMary%20Jane%20Copps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMary%20Jane%20Copps%2C%20a%20conversation%20coach%2C%20said%20phone%20call%20anxiety%20is%20prevalent%20among%20young%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECopps%20said%20young%20people%20lack%20practice%20in%20handling%20uncertain%2C%20spontaneous%20dialogue.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECopps%20said%20executives%20recognize%20the%20value%20of%20communication%20but%20often%20don't%20invest%20in%20training%20staff.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Mary%20Jane%20Copps%2C%20a%20communication%20coach%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Phone%20Lady.%26quot%3B%20Copps%20has%20spent%20two%20decades%20coaching%20people%20at%20the%20workplace%20on%20how%20to%20be%20better%20communicators.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20%26quot%3BThe%20Phone%20Lady%26quot%3B%20for%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20my%20company%2C%20phone%20anxiety%20wasn't%20something%20my%20clients%20talked%20about.%20Companies%20hired%20me%20to%20help%20their%20teams%20have%20better%20conversations%2C%20and%20for%20the%20first%2012%20years%2C%20those%20conversations%20mostly%20happened%20over%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20eight%20to%2010%20years%20ago%2C%20that%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20I%20coach%20people%20of%20every%20generation%20who%20struggle%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-workers-genz-millennials-avoiding-phone-calls-paying-a-price-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereal-time%20conversations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20see%20it%20most%20often%20among%20younger%20employees%20entering%20the%20workforce%2C%20and%20the%20issue%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20it%20seems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c172785-f88e-435c-b315-a7034bcbe9f0%5C%22%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20is%20uncertainty%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople's%20reasons%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapps-to-overcome-phone-call-anxiety-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ephone%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20deeply%20personal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20with%20one%20man%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20family%20that%20struggled%20financially.%20Whenever%20the%20phone%20rang%2C%20his%20mother%20refused%20to%20answer%20because%20it%20was%20usually%20someone%20they%20owed%20money%20to.%20He%20learned%20early%20that%20answering%20the%20phone%20meant%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20something%20I%20hear%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20People%20aren't%20afraid%20of%20talking.%20They're%20afraid%20of%20not%20knowing%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20they%20say%20hello.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20we%20don't%20get%20practice%20handling%20uncertainty%20anymore%20is%20that%20our%20phones%20aren't%20really%20phones%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20send%20a%20text%20or%20an%20email%2C%20you%20can%20think%20about%20it%2C%20edit%20it%2C%20and%20reply%20whenever%20you're%20ready.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-phone-ansewring-hello-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ephone%20conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20have%20to%20improvise.%20You%20have%20to%20think%20on%20your%20feet.%20Once%20you've%20said%20something%2C%20you%20can't%20take%20it%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20generations%20developed%20that%20skill%20naturally%20because%20they%20grew%20up%20with%20a%20phone%20hanging%20on%20the%20kitchen%20wall%2C%20but%20the%20younger%20generation%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20rise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-twitter-facebook-political-polarization-mechanism-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we're%20kind%20of%20in%20silos.%20We're%20not%20all%20watching%20the%20same%20news%20program%20in%20the%20evening.%20We%20have%20less%20in%20common%20when%20we%20meet%20a%20stranger.%20That%20prevents%20us%20from%20having%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20talking%20became%20a%20skill%20instead%20of%20something%20we%20assume%20everyone%20knows%20how%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225c0d8503-d8c4-413e-b2b4-669b810abf2f%5C%22%3EThe%20conversation%20gap%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20I%20survey%20executives%20about%20workplace%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20past%20year%2C%2098%25%20of%20senior%20executives%20told%20me%20that%20the%20ability%20to%20have%20real-time%20conversations%20is%20vital%20to%20business%20success.%20Only%2011%25%20believed%20their%20organizations%20were%20doing%20it%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20call%20that%20the%20conversation%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20found%20that%20many%20tech%20companies%20want%20employees%20with%20strong%20communication%20skills%2C%20but%20aren't%20interested%20in%20training%20them.%20Instead%2C%20they're%20hoping%20to%20hire%20people%20who%20already%20have%20those%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20problem%20because%20communication%20is%20often%20dismissed%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cofounder-sergey-brin-game-go-the-future-of-work-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoft%20skill%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20The%20term%20actually%20comes%20from%20the%20military%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20where%20organizational%20skills%2C%20writing%2C%20and%20speaking%20were%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bsoft%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20operating%20machinery%20was%20considered%20%26quot%3Bhard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20label%20makes%20communication%20sound%20optional%20when%20it's%20actually%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeaders%20set%20the%20tone.%20If%20executives%20don't%20model%20good%20conversations%20or%20encourage%20real-time%20communication%2C%20their%20teams%20won't%20either.%20Organizations%20need%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20these%20skills%20matter%20and%20that%20employees%20will%20be%20supported%20if%20they%20need%20help%20developing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bdd564a5-ee34-4b05-8fe3-c1408267a78e%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20practice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkelsey-hightower-google-distinguished-engineer-tips-for-new-graduates-ai-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econversation%20is%20a%20skill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20skills%20can%20be%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20with%20people%20you%20already%20know.%20Call%20your%20grandmother.%20Call%20your%20sister.%20If%20you're%20used%20to%20texting%20your%20friends%2C%20spend%20one%20weekend%20calling%20them%20instead.%20You%20might%20want%20to%20warn%20them%20first%2C%20so%20they%20actually%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20with%20friends%2C%20put%20your%20phone%20away.%20Focus%20on%20the%20conversation%20instead%20of%20constantly%20checking%20your%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20start%20practicing%20small%20talk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20dislike%20it%2C%20but%20when%20you%20begin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-way-to-handle-tell-me-about-yourself-job-interview-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20attend%20a%20conference%2C%20or%20walk%20into%20a%20meeting%2C%20small%20talk%20is%20everywhere.%20Keep%20a%20few%20simple%20topics%20in%20your%20back%20pocket%20%E2%80%94%20vacations%2C%20movies%2C%20the%20weather%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you%20can%20practice%20having%20conversations%20without%20worrying%20about%20achieving%20a%20specific%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20young%20salesperson%20I%20coached%20later%20told%20me%20he%20started%20using%20the%20techniques%20I'd%20taught%20at%20home%20with%20his%20wife.%20They%20began%20asking%20each%20other%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-ask-these-two-questions-in-every-job-interview-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopen-ended%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20dinner%2C%20and%20he%20said%20it%20improved%20their%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20conversation%20doesn't%20just%20make%20us%20better%20employees.%20It%20makes%20us%20better%20partners%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20family%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20we%20should%20point%20fingers%20at%20younger%20generations.%20Technology%20has%20changed%20all%20of%20us.%20We're%20overwhelmed%2C%20overscheduled%2C%20and%20constantly%20distracted.%20We%20even%20schedule%20phone%20calls%20with%20close%20friends%20and%20family%20because%20everyone%20is%20so%20busy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20want%20better%20relationships%20%E2%80%94%20at%20work%20and%20at%20home%20%E2%80%94%20we%20have%20to%20make%20time%20to%20practice%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunication-coach-phone-call-anxiety-gen-z-millennials-workplace-careers-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17833