%2C%22published%22%3A1783296149000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Face%2Fbranded_news%2F1200%2Fcpsprodpb%2Fd46d%2Flive%2F7b635980-75f2-11f1-8c3f-e37c76e39331.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcy4e1lzwgvxo%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Relations%20between%20Dhaka%20and%20Delhi%2C%20that%20turned%20frosty%20under%20the%20interim%20government%2C%20are%20on%20the%20mend.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A94%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcy4e1lzwgvxo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20decades%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20a%20former%20Apple%20and%20Amazon%20engineer%20started%20an%20AI%20chip%20company%20in%20his%20mid-50s%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222087%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stephen%20Huang%2C%20Founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Tranxform%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a38f857c7a58f814f0d4e06%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221565%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStephen%20Huang%2C%20Founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Tranxform%2C%20participated%20in%20a%20demo%20at%20the%20Computex%20trade%20show%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Huang%2FTranxform%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20decades%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20Stephen%20Huang%2C%2055%2C%20launched%20AI%20chip%20startup%20Tranxform.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETranxform%20is%20trying%20to%20build%20more%20efficient%20AI%20processors%20and%20recruit%20top%20talent%20in%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHuang%20says%20AI%20hardware%20favors%20deep%20experience%20over%20youthful%20speed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStephen%20Huang%20had%20spent%20decades%20building%20chips%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT's%20launch%3C%2Fa%3E%20convinced%20him%20the%20market%20was%20ready%20for%20the%20AI%20chip%20company%20he%20had%20long%20considered%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20Huang%20had%20worked%20on%20MediaTek's%20GPUs%2C%20Apple's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFace%20ID%20technology%2C%20and%20at%20an%20Amazon%20AI%20chip%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20ChatGPT%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene%20in%20late%202022%2C%20Huang%20became%20convinced%20the%20industry%20had%20reached%20a%20turning%20point.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20the%20market%20had%20arrived%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20at%2055%2C%20Huang%20decided%20to%20start%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20he%20founded%20Tranxform%20AI%2C%20a%20Taiwan-based%20AI%20chip%20startup%20developing%20power-efficient%20processors%20designed%20to%20run%20AI%20models%20outside%20large%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20now%20employs%20about%2040%20people%20and%20is%20preparing%20its%20first%20chip%2C%20which%20Huang%20expects%20to%20be%20ready%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20is%20among%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20entrepreneurs%20chasing%20opportunities%20created%20by%20the%20AI%20boom.%20Unlike%20many%20founders%20building%20companies%20around%20large%20language%20models%2C%20however%2C%20he%20spent%20decades%20designing%20chips%20before%20launching%20his%20own%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Huang%20never%20viewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturning-40-midlife-crisis-career-rebrand-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eage%20as%20a%20disadvantage.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsmc-billionaire-founder-morris-chang-lessons-business-leadership-advice-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMorris%20Chang%3C%2Fa%3E%20started%20TSMC%20in%20his%2050s%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsm-stock-price-valuation-ai-demand-nvda-tech-earnings-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETaiwan%20Semiconductor%20Manufacturing%20Company%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20founded%20the%20world's%20largest%20contract%20chipmaker%20at%2055.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Huang%20believes%20age%20may%20be%20on%20his%20side%2C%20arguing%20that%20hardware%20startups%20often%20favor%20experience%20in%20ways%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-founders-raising-millions-for-their-ai-startups-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20do%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESemiconductor%20design%20is%20a%20long%20game%2C%20he%20said.%20Building%20a%20system-on-a-chip%20%E2%80%94%20the%20integrated%20processor%20that%20powers%20devices%20ranging%20from%20smartphones%20to%20AI%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20requires%20balancing%20countless%20tradeoffs%20across%20hardware%20and%20software%2C%20a%20skill%20that%20can%20take%20decades%20to%20develop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20build%20a%20good%20SoC%2C%20you%20need%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Huang%20said.%20%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20you%20would%20not%20know%20how%20to%20balance%20different%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang's%20startup%20adventure%20was%20not%20an%20obvious%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20founding%20Tranxform%2C%20he%20had%20a%20stable%20career%20and%20a%20comfortable%20income%20in%20the%20US.%20Building%20the%20company%20meant%20taking%20a%20significant%20risk%20and%20spending%20most%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20a%20decision%20his%20family%20initially%20struggled%20to%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Tranxform%20grew%20and%20reached%20key%20milestones%2C%20his%20family's%20attitude%20changed.%20%26quot%3BToday%2C%20they%20are%20proud%20of%20what%20we%20have%20accomplished%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20also%20helped.%20Huang's%20two%20sons%20were%20adults%20when%20he%20founded%20the%20company.%20One%20works%20in%20the%20technology%20industry%2C%20while%20the%20other%20recently%20graduated%20from%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20them%20become%20independent%20has%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20me%20to%20dedicate%20the%20time%20and%20energy%20needed%20to%20build%20Tranxform%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebelieved%20the%20risk%20was%20worth%20taking%20because%20demand%20for%20specialized%20AI%20hardware%20would%20continue%20growing%20as%20companies%20looked%20for%20faster%20and%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-us-chips-electricity-power-crunch-shortage-goldman-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenergy-efficient%20ways%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20run%20increasingly%20complex%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang's%20optimism%20comes%20as%20investors%20pour%20fresh%20capital%20into%20AI%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20funding%20for%20AI%20and%20machine-learning%20chip%20startups%20rose%20over%2070%25%20to%20%2416.2%20billion%20in%202025%20from%20the%20year%20before%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook.%20However%2C%20the%20number%20of%20deals%20fell%20to%20232%20from%20266%20in%20the%20same%20period%20as%20investors%20increasingly%20wrote%20bigger%20checks%20to%20a%20smaller%20cohort%20of%20potential%20breakout%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20funding%20stood%20at%20%249.9%20billion%20as%20of%20June%2022%2C%20with%20deal%20counts%20at%2087%2C%20per%20PitchBook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6MOxj%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Column%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6MOxj%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc9f6926-40cb-46e0-b614-8cf6d6b84fc8%5C%22%3EReturning%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20AI%20drew%20Huang%20toward%20entrepreneurship%2C%20Silicon%20Valley's%20intensifying%20talent%20wars%20made%20him%20rethink%20where%20to%20build%20his%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20taught%20him%20how%20difficult%20it%20was%20for%20startups%20to%20compete%20with%20tech%20giants%20such%20as%20Google%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Nvidia%20for%20engineering%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20kept%20training%20people%2C%20and%20they%20got%20poached%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang%20built%20his%20company%20in%20the%20Taiwanese%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaiwan-tsmc-semiconductor-chips-hsinchu-birth-rate-fertility-children-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echip%20hub%20of%20Hsinchu%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20he%20believed%20he%20could%20assemble%20a%20more%20stable%20engineering%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20recruits%20was%20his%20college%20classmate%20Way-Shing%20Lee%2C%20who%20joined%20Tranxform%20as%20chief%20technology%20officer%20last%20year%20after%20retiring%20from%20the%20US%20chip%20giant%20Qualcomm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221108%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Way-Shing%20Lee%20and%20Stephen%20Huang%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3b73606891755ad48b855e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221477%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20Huang's%20(right)%20key%20recruits%20was%20college%20classmate%20Way-Shing%20Lee%20(left)%2C%20who%20is%20now%20Tranxform's%20CTO.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Huang%2FTranxform%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20startup%20life%20has%20replaced%20the%20stability%20of%20Huang's%20previous%20career%20with%20fundraising%2C%20recruiting%2C%20customer%20meetings%2C%20and%20constant%20technical%20problem-solving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStarting%20a%20company%20is%20very%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20Huang%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20find%20business%20partners.%20You%20have%20to%20sell%20your%20story.%20You%20have%20to%20find%20funding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuang%20said%20Tranxform%20is%20preparing%20for%20its%20next%20fundraising%20round%2C%20declining%20to%20disclose%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20licensing%20and%20generates%20little%20revenue%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Huang%20believes%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-wall-street-tech-selloff-ai-token-goldman-sachs-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20opportunities%20in%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20remain%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20industry%20is%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20just%20getting%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-apple-amazon-engineer-starts-ai-chip-company-50s-transxform-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783296001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a38f818f4bed3c6152cc7a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-apple-amazon-engineer-starts-ai-chip-company-50s-transxform-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20AI%20boom%20has%20produced%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20founders%20racing%20to%20build%20companies%20around%20emergent%20technoloy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22htan%40insider.com%20(Huileng%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20left%20Google%20and%20spent%20a%20year%20traveling.%206%20months%20on%20a%20Thai%20island%20led%20me%20to%20a%20career%20I%20never%20expected.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20painting%20on%20an%20island%20in%20Thailand.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45c39eec11c5f7e7fa76ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESara%20Wilczynska%20took%20a%20yearlong%20career%20break%20and%20discovered%20watercolor%20while%20traveling%20in%20Thailand%2C%20setting%20her%20on%20the%20path%20to%20a%20new%20career.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESara%20Wilczynska%20grew%20up%20in%20Poland%20and%20built%20her%20career%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20in%20offices%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20found%20the%20pace%20at%20Google%20in%20the%20US%20unsustainable%2C%20so%20she%20quit%20and%20traveled%20with%20her%20partner%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20watercolor%20hobby%20she%20picked%20up%20on%20a%20Thai%20island%20turned%20into%20a%20new%20career%2C%20leading%20her%20to%20open%20an%20art%20studio%20in%20San%20Diego.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sara%20Wilczynska%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Swil%20Arts%20Studio.%20She%20left%20her%20job%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Google%2C%20spent%20a%20year%20traveling%20with%20her%20partner%2C%20and%20discovered%20watercolors%20in%20Thailand.%20Her%20words%20have%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Warsaw%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20Poland%20was%20still%20a%20communist%20country.%20I%20remember%20witnessing%20the%20shift%20into%20capitalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20earned%20a%20master's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freason-incoming-freshman-wants-computer-science-degree-despite-ai-fears-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edegree%20in%20computer%20science%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Warsaw%2C%20interning%20in%20Barcelona%20and%20studying%20abroad%20in%20Edinburgh%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2025%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20London%20to%20work%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20an%20investment%20bank.%20I%20stayed%20nearly%20five%20years%2C%20but%20even%20then%2C%20there%20was%20a%20quiet%20voice%20in%20the%20background%20asking%20whether%20this%20was%20really%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfc5f819-2351-49fb-b46c-eef863bc1ffa%5C%22%3EI%20started%20working%20at%20Google%20in%202015%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Google%20in%20Zurich%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20step%20closer%20to%20something%20more%20meaningful.%20After%20about%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20I%20got%20my%20US%20visa%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-new-york-city-different-than-visiting-lessons-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etransferred%20to%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20news%20section%20of%20the%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20my%20career%20was%20everything%20I%20had%20worked%20toward.%20Google%20was%20flexible%2C%20supportive%2C%20and%20full%20of%20brilliant%20people.%20I%20had%20autonomy%20over%20my%20work%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20projects%20to%20my%20physical%20working%20location%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-loyalty-corporate-america-dysfunction-employers-employees-att-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebenefits%20were%20incredible%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20standing%20with%20New%20York%20City%20in%20the%20Background.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45de6a2680585ce91a3750%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223036%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20she%20got%20her%20US%20visa%2C%20she%20was%20transferred%20to%20New%20York%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20days%20included%20coding%2C%20meetings%2C%20but%20also%20yoga%20classes%2C%20gym%20sessions%2C%20gourmet%20birthday%20meals%2C%20and%20even%20subsidized%20massages.%20There%20was%20also%20stability%20%E2%80%94%20a%20good%20paycheck%20and%20stock%20grant%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20also%20what%20made%20it%20so%20hard%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20as%20my%20career%20progressed%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20promoted%20twice%20within%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20there%20was%20more%20high-level%20work%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20stakeholder%20meetings%2C%20and%20less%20hands-on%20coding%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20feel%20disconnected.%20A%20growing%20sense%20that%20the%20pace%20wasn't%20sustainable%20for%20me.%20That%20constant%20stimulation%20%E2%80%94%20screens%2C%20deadlines%2C%20notifications%2C%20expectations%20%E2%80%94%20was%20pulling%20me%20away%20from%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20later%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20San%20Diego%20with%20my%20partner%2C%20Valentina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2284c228e8-d7e6-427e-8763-b36f2ab58e83%5C%22%3ESomething%20shifted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flived-in-different-cities-to-find-dream-home-san-diego-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20San%20Diego%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20forced%20me%20to%20slow%20down.%20There%20was%20nature%20everywhere%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ocean%2C%20the%20desert%2C%20the%20mountains%20%E2%80%94%20and%20suddenly%20I%20had%20space%20to%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20noticing%20small%20things%20again.%20The%20scent%20of%20jasmine%20on%20a%20warm%20evening.%20The%20simple%20joy%20of%20eating%20a%20fish%20taco.%20That%20realization%20made%20it%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20the%20misalignment%20in%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20fix%20it%20without%20leaving.%20I%20trained%20in%20sound%20healing%20and%20hosted%20sessions.%20I%20took%20on%20different%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-project-eat-ai-infrastructure-tools-chips-artificial-intelligence-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprojects%20at%20Google%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20leading%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20initiatives.%20I%20even%20reduced%20my%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20it%20fully%20addressed%20the%20core%20feeling.%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BAm%20I%20just%20being%20too%20picky%3F%20Am%20I%20asking%20for%20too%20much%3F%26quot%3B%20Because%20there%20was%20nothing%20objectively%20wrong%20with%20my%20job.%20It%20wasn't%20toxic.%20I%20respected%20my%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20I%20understood%20that%20a%20job%20can%20tick%20every%20box%20%E2%80%94%20it%20can%20look%20perfect%20on%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20something%20deeper%20is%20missing%2C%20it's%20not%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20leaving%20wasn't%20easy.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20was%20not%20knowing%20what%20would%20come%20next.%20I%20kept%20thinking%20I%20needed%20a%20plan.%20A%20clear%2C%20logical%20next%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20eventually%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20waiting%20for%20certainty%20was%20just%20keeping%20me%20stuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20made%20a%20decision%20that%20felt%20radical%20at%20the%20time.%20I%20quit%20my%20job%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%20%E2%80%94%20Valentina's%20job%20had%20been%20eliminated%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadult-gap-year-quit-job-travel-the-world-career-pivot-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etravel%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%20We%20rented%20out%20our%20apartment%20in%20San%20Diego%20and%20went%20traveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20standing%20by%20the%20sea%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45dfc6ec11c5f7e7fa7733%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20couple%20left%20San%20Diego%20and%20traveled%20for%20a%20year.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292bc563b-549a-4704-b674-ebe867f70c64%5C%22%3EThat%20year%20changed%20everything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spent%20most%20of%202023%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20with%20shorter%20trips%20to%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20At%20first%2C%20we%20moved%20quickly%2C%20but%20eventually%20we%20slowed%20down.%20We%20spent%20six%20months%20in%20Koh%20Tao%2C%20a%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkoh-samui-thailand-expat-life-abroad-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eisland%20in%20Thailand%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELife%20there%20felt%20simple.%20My%20partner%20was%20working%20as%20a%20dive%20master%2C%20and%20I%20had%20something%20I%20hadn't%20experienced%20in%20years%3A%20unstructured%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20picked%20up%20watercolors.%20I%20had%20no%20formal%20training.%20I%20just%20felt%20drawn%20to%20it.%20I%20started%20taking%20online%20classes%2C%20sketching%20scenes%20from%20the%20island%3A%20fruit%20stands%2C%20village%20views%2C%20little%20everyday%20moments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20sharing%20my%20work%20in%20local%20Facebook%20community%20groups%20in%20Koh%20Tao.%20I%20didn't%20expect%20much%2C%20but%20people%20began%20reaching%20out%20on%20Facebook%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20to%20compliment%20the%20work%2C%20but%20to%20buy%20it.%20They%20would%20tell%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20captures%20my%20memory%20of%20this%20place%20perfectly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburned-out-late-20s-quit-job-travel-career-break-travelries-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyear%20of%20travel%20%3C%2Fa%3Eended%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20commit%20to%20art.%20Not%20because%20I%20had%20everything%20figured%20out%2C%20but%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20ignore%20that%20pull%20anymore.%20We%20extended%20our%20flexible%20lifestyle%20%E2%80%94%20house-sitting%20across%20the%20US%20to%20reduce%20living%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20started%20building%20my%20studio%2C%20Swil%20Arts%2C%20in%20San%20Diego%2C%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20painting%20palm%20trees%20and%20a%20tatoo%20on%20their%20arm.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45e04a1aaffe3020cb1f95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWilczynska%20now%20runs%20Swil%20Arts%20studio%20in%20San%20Diego.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Sara%20Wilczynska%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20that's%20where%20I%20create%20original%20watercolor%20illustrations.%20Then%20I%20reproduce%20them%20as%20illustrated%20goods%2C%20including%20prints%20and%20homeware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20days%20are%20very%20different%20now.%20I%20spend%20mornings%20painting%2C%20afternoons%20on%20the%20business%20side%2C%20handling%20client%20communications%2C%20website%20content%2C%20and%20business%20strategy.%20I%20earn%20my%20income%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tests-prime-shipping-web-without-amazon-login-shopify-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edirect-to-consumer%20retail%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wholesale%20partnerships%20with%20boutiques%2C%20and%20custom%20art%20commissions%20for%20both%20individuals%20and%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it's%20not%20at%20the%20level%20of%20my%20previous%20income%2C%20we%20are%20still%20a%20young%20company.%20Success%20is%20completely%20different%20now.%20It's%20not%20about%20productivity%20or%20output.%20It's%20about%20impact.%20If%20one%20person%20pauses%20because%20of%20my%20work%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20feel%20something%2C%20remember%20something%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-google-travel-thailand-watercolor-success-art-studio-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783295281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F